<subSubSection id="C36965D095601871FF33B0C5172E1F27" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95601871FF33B0C5172E1F27" blockId="4.[166,1225,1431,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
D i a g n o s i s. Wingspan 
<quantity id="4C8B9BBE95601871FDE6B0CA11C31F07" box="[526,646,1527,1554]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="12.5" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="9.0">9–16 mm</quantity>
. Head white with brownish scales. Thorax pale fuscous. Forewings white, suffused whitish brown and dark fuscous dots (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FBECB32A17041F27" box="[1028,1089,1559,1586]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[236,1125,179,972]" captionTargetId="figure-336@4.[232,1167,171,985]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Kessleria saxifragae: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FBA5B325171E1F27" box="[1101,1115,1560,1586]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1408,1430]" captionTargetBox="[325,1069,174,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-159@1.[321,1078,171,1383]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Argyresthia kurenzovi: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral view, 3 — ventral plate, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — female genitalia; 6 — bursa copulatrix with signum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414497/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FBA5B325171E1F27" box="[1101,1115,1560,1586]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36965D095601871FF33B30A12921FC7" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95601871FF33B30A10C61F67" blockId="4.[166,1225,1431,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FE64B30A128D1F47" box="[396,456,1591,1618]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[236,1125,179,972]" captionTargetId="figure-336@4.[232,1167,171,985]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Kessleria saxifragae: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FE39B305129A1F47" box="[465,479,1592,1618]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[322,1065,191,1089]" captionTargetId="figure-253@2.[317,1074,174,1089]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Argyresthia communana: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral plate, 3 — valva, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414501/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FE39B305129A1F47" box="[465,479,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FE03B30512BC1F47" box="[491,505,1592,1618]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1063,1085]" captionTargetBox="[334,1055,174,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-291@3.[321,1078,171,1046]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Paradoxus osyridellus: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414505/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FE03B30512BC1F47" box="[491,505,1592,1618]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Valva of elongated elliptoid shape with large sacculus (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FB6AB30A17811F47" box="[1154,1220,1591,1618]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[236,1125,179,972]" captionTargetId="figure-336@4.[232,1167,171,985]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Kessleria saxifragae: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FF4EB36513F11F67" box="[166,180,1624,1650]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[166,199,1105,1127]" captionTargetBox="[322,1065,191,1089]" captionTargetId="figure-253@2.[317,1074,174,1089]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 2. Argyresthia communana: 1 — forewing pattern; 2–4 — male genitalia (2 — ventral plate, 3 — valva, 4 — aedeagus); 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414501" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414501/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FF4EB36513F11F67" box="[166,180,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus long, about three times as long as valva (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FCF4B36A101C1F67" box="[796,857,1623,1650]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[236,1125,179,972]" captionTargetId="figure-336@4.[232,1167,171,985]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Kessleria saxifragae: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">fig. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FC8CB36510371F67" box="[868,882,1624,1650]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1063,1085]" captionTargetBox="[334,1055,174,1028]" captionTargetId="figure-291@3.[321,1078,171,1046]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Paradoxus osyridellus: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414505" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414505/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FC8CB36510371F67" box="[868,882,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC365B95601871FF33B34A12921FC7" blockId="4.[166,1225,1431,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FE46B34A114C1F87" box="[430,521,1655,1682]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[236,1125,179,972]" captionTargetId="figure-336@4.[232,1167,171,985]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Kessleria saxifragae: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
fig. 4, 
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FE13B345114C1F87" box="[507,521,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">4</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FDF1B34511621F87" box="[537,551,1656,1682]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1289,1311]" captionTargetBox="[331,1074,184,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-183@5.[326,1083,166,1269]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 5. Pseudoplutella porrectella: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (lateral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414511" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414511/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FDF1B34511621F87" box="[537,551,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">5</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Lobes of vaginal plate moderate and not close to each other. Apophyses posterior almost equal to apophyses anterior (
<figureCitation id="13482ADE95601871FC7FB3AA10AB1FA7" box="[919,1006,1687,1714]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[170,203,990,1012]" captionTargetBox="[236,1125,179,972]" captionTargetId="figure-336@4.[232,1167,171,985]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 4. Kessleria saxifragae: 1 — moth (habitus, dorsal); 2 — male genitalia (ventral view); 3 — aedeagus; 4 — female genitalia; 5 — bursa copulatrix." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6414507" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6414507/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
fig. 4, 
<emphasis id="B907EA4995601871FC08B3A510AB1FA7" box="[992,1006,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">4</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). 
